title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
January 12, 2016

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate





	Winfield D. Ong, of Indiana, to be United States District Judge for the Southern District of Indiana, vice Sarah Evans Barker, retired.

	Donald Karl Schott, of Wisconsin, to be United States Circuit Judge for the Seventh Circuit, vice Terence T. Evans, deceased.

	Myra C. Selby, of Indiana, to be United States Circuit Judge for the Seventh Circuit, vice John Daniel Tinder, retired.
